The class constructor initializes the node pointers to NULL when an instance of the class is declared/allocated, not when new node is called. If that were the case then for every added node I would loose the pointers to the previously added pointers.

/* nodeLinkClass constructor */
nodeLinkClass::nodeLinkClass()
{
    this->is_poweron_handler          = NULL;
    for(unsigned int i=0; i<MAX_NODES; ++i)
    {
        this->node_ptrs[i]            = NULL;
    }
}

In any case, I don't need to free these pointers in the destructor.

